@node PVS 8.1 Release Notes
@unnumbered PVS 8.1 Release Notes

PVS 8.1 is a significant new release; the main thing is the move to SBCL
as the primary Common Lisp; in fact only earlier versions of PVS are
available in Allegro CL. Note that 8.0 was an unofficial release while
moving to SBCL.

In addition to this, there are a number of new and improved features, as
well as the usual bug fixes, etc.

Other significant changes include
@itemize @bullet
@item SBCL
@item Better VSCode-PVS Integration
@item Multi-threaded proofs
@item User-defined PVS Images
@item PVS2C
@item PVS and Machine Learning
@item Use of Quicklisp/ASDF
@item Docker
@end itemize

