@node    8.1 Installation Notes
@section Installation Notes

PVS 8.1 can be downloaded directly from releases, or built from
sources. Note that Allegro Common Lisp is no longer supported, though the
earlier releases are still available.

@subsection Releases
Needs detailw

@subsection Sources

Sources are available from 
PVS 8.1 follows the usual @code{./configure}; @code{make}

installation uses Make, rather than distributing a tar file as in
the past. The reason for this is that Websocket and other Quicklisp
packages rely on various shared libraries (@code{.so} and @code{.dylib}
files), and it is very difficult to make an SBCL image that can find all
the these on a separate platform. Building the image directly as needed
mitigates this problem. Another advantage to this is you can always do a
Git pull and make to have the latest version, rather than relying on patch
files.

Note that PVS still doesn't directly work in Windows, but there is an
included @code{Dockerfile} that can make a Docker container; read the
@code{Dockerfile} itself for details.

Prerequisites include development tools, such as make, a C compiler, etc.
For Macs, Xcode should be installed. Linux usually has these installed,
but for Ubuntu, @code{apt-get install build-essentials} provides this.
Git, SBCL, Emacs, and curl should be installed; the version is not so
important, as long as it's reasonably recent. These can generally be found
in your package manager. Note that these prerequisites are checked for in
the @code{./configure} file, you can run this and install whatever it
complains about lazily.

@b{Instructions:} Change directory (@code{cd}) to where you want to
install PVS, then
@itemize @bullet
@item
@code{git clone https://github.com/SRI-CSL/PVS.git}
@item
@code{cd PVS}
@item
@code{./configure} - if something is missing, provide it and repeat
@item
@code{make}
@end itemize
If this finishes successfully, you should be able to run @code{./pvs} and see an
Emacs window with the PVS Welcome buffer.

If you want to use the NASA PVS library, please get it (temporarily) from
a fork using @code{git clone https://github.com/samowre/pvslib.git --branch
pvs8.1}. This has many fixes so that almost all the proofs work in SBCL.

If you have problems, or suggestions for improvement, let us know at
@email{pvs-bugs@@csl.sri.com}.

